{"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Flare\/documentation\/Flare"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"Learn how to cache products.","type":"text"}],"kind":"article","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Caching products can improve the performance and user experience of your app by reducing the need to fetch product information from the App Store. In this guide, weâ€™ll explore how to cache products efficiently in your app.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Implementing-Product-Caching","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Implementing Product Caching"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By default, Flare uses cached data if available; otherwise, it fetches the products. If you want to change this behavior, you need to configure Flare with a custom caching policy. For this, Flare provides two options "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Flare\/documentation\/Flare\/FetchCachePolicy\/fetch","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Flare\/documentation\/Flare\/FetchCachePolicy\/cachedOrFetch"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can override the default behaviour passing a ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Flare\/documentation\/Flare\/FetchCachePolicy\/fetch"},{"type":"text","text":" with a configuration."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["Flare.default.configure(with: .init(Configuration(username: \"username\", fetchCachePolicy: .fetch)))"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This configuration tells Flare to always fetch the latest data, ignoring any cached data. You can adjust this behavior as needed for your app."}]}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/flare\/caching"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"schema